Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While it boils, trim the @green beans{150%grams} and cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Lamb Mince and Beans ==

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Next, add the @lamb mince{200%grams} and fry until the mince has browned and the beans have started to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

== Sauce ==

While the mince and beans cook, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%grams}, @korma curry paste{50%grams} and @curry powder mix{1%sachet} to the mince and fry, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @water{175%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Finishing ==

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @mango chutney{40%grams}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the lamb mince masala.

Enjoy!